race.comment: BUCCLEUCH (1) resumes here. He looked a very progressive 2yo over the Winter which culminated in a dominant win in the Taj Rossi Final, backed into $1.45 there with 59kg. He's been kept on ice since that win and kicks off here in a BM70 which he's no doubt up to winning. 59.5kg after a 3kg claim is no easy feat against some progressive horses right down in the weights, but he is the class. SASS APPEAL (8) gets in very light after her claim. She won well at Seymour at $1.85 last time out and will be very hard to beat again. JEWEL BANDIT (2) has been big odds in both starts but proved the punters wrong with solid wins. To 1400m now should be okay, don't expect $21 or $41 this time. THE VOLTA (4) is racing well and maps for a very soft run just behind the speed. OUR JUSTIFY (10) won her maiden well at Mornington last time and can improve again to 1400m.
